New @ Hoover's: Metwood, Inc.
==================================================
Metwood shapes the future of residential and commercial construction
with its patented, steel-and-wood headers and girders for building
supports. The combination increases load strength and structural
integrity, allowing for structural designs that couldn't be produced
with wood alone. Other products include floor joists and light-gauge
steel trusses. Metwood also engineers and designs garage, deck, and
porch concrete pour-over systems. Contractors and do-it-yourselfers in
Virginia and North Carolina generate most sales; lumberyards,
home-improvement stores, and hardware stores make up about 20%.
Founders Robert Callahan (CEO) and Ronald Shiflett (VP) respectively
own about 46% and 18% of Metwood.

Company capsule for Metwood, Inc.:
http://communication.hoovers.com/cgi-bin13/DM?y=eCya0LEDJZ0Bk40CCN0Ak

By Melanie Robertson
mrobertson@hoovers.com
Manufacturing & Industry Editorial Team

