Executives On The Move
For the week of January 6, 2003
Full list, capsule links, and officer biographies at
http://communication.hoovers.com/cgi-bin13/DM?y=eCya0LEDJZ0Bk40B3u0A7

Name: Mitchell G. Leibovitz
Background Information: Leibovitz is retiring as chairman and CEO of
auto parts and services chain The Pep Boys -- Manny, Moe & Jack upon
the appointment of a successor.
Additional Information: He's been the CEO with The Pep Boys since
1984. An executive search committee is searching for Leibovitz's
replacement.

Name: Rick D. Puckett
Background Information: Puckett was appointed VP, CFO, and treasurer
at United Natural Foods, Inc., a national distributor of natural and
organic foods in the US.
Additional Information: Puckett, who held several executive positions
with Suntory Water Group Inc., succeeds Todd Weintraub.

Name: Michael G. Wokasch
Background Information:  Wokasch has been named COO at Impax
Laboratories, Inc., a maker of specialty generic pharmaceuticals.
Additional Information: He was previously president with Aurora
Biosciences Corporation. Wokasch succeeds Larry Hsu, who remains
Impax's president.

